{
  "chapterTitle": "House 1",
  "notes": "The opening of the Kesh Temple Hymn describes the divine origins of the temple, its praise by Enlil, and its architectural majesty, comparing it to the Abzu and the mountains.",
  "chunks": [
    {
      "originalText": "nam2-nun-e nam2-nun-e e2-ta nam-ta-ab-ed2\nden-lil2 nam2-nun-e e2-ta nam-ta-ab-ed2\nnam2-nun-e nam-lugal-la e2-ta nam-ta-ab-ed2\n",
      "translatedText": "The princely one, the princely one, from the house came forth,\nEnlil, the princely one, from the house came forth,\nThe princely one, in kingship, from the house came forth.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "den-lil2 kur-kur-ra igi mi-ni-in-il2-il2-i\nden-lil2-ra kur ni2-ba mu-na-il2-il2-i\n",
      "translatedText": "Enlil upon the lands his eyes did lift and gaze,\nTo Enlil all the lands their own heads lift and raise.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "an ub-da 4 den-lil2-ra jickiri6-gin7 mu-na-sig7\nkecki saj il2 mu-na-ni-in-jal2\n",
      "translatedText": "The four corners of heaven for Enlil like a garden grew green,\nAnd Kesh with its head held high was a sight to be seen.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "kecki kur-kur-ra saj il2-bi\nden-lil2-le kecki za3-mi2 am3-ma-ab-be2\n",
      "translatedText": "Kesh, among the lands, its head is lifted high,\nEnlil for Kesh a song of praise did then glorify.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "dnisaba nu-ka-ac-bi-im\ninim-bi-ta sa-gin7 im-da-an-sur\n",
      "translatedText": "Nisaba was its arbiter, its word and its guide,\nWith those words, like a net, she wove them side by side.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "dub-ba sar-sar cu-ce3 al-ja2-ja2\ne2 muc3 kalam-ma gud huc aratta\ne2 kecki muc3 kalam-ma gud huc aratta\n",
      "translatedText": "Written on the tablets, held within the hand,\nHouse, the jewel of the land, fierce bull of Aratta's land,\nHouse of Kesh, the jewel of the land, fierce bull of Aratta's land.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "hur-saj-da mu2-a an-da gu2 la2-a\ne2-kur-da mu2-a kur-ra saj il2-bi\n",
      "translatedText": "Grown with the mountain, reaching to the sky,\nGrown with the Ekur, lifting its head on high.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "abzu-gin7 ri-a hur-saj-gin7 sig7-sig7-ga\nkecki-gin7 rib-ba lu2 ci-in-ga-tum2-mu\n",
      "translatedText": "Founded like the Abzu, green like the mountain range,\nWill any man bring forth a thing so great and strange?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "ur-saj-bi dacac7-gi4-gin7 rib-ba ama ci-in-ga-u3-tud\nnin-bi dnin-tud-gin7 rib-ba-ra a-ba-a igi mu-ni-in-du8\n",
      "translatedText": "Will any mother bear a hero like Ashgi, so bold?\nWho has seen a lady like Nintud, of beauty untold?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 1-kam-ma",
      "translatedText": "The first house.",
      "type": "verse"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapterTitle": "House 2",
  "notes": "The second house of the Kesh Temple Hymn describes the temple's physical and spiritual grandeur using maritime and celestial imagery, emphasizing its foundation in the Abzu and its reach toward the heavens.",
  "chunks": [
    {
      "originalText": "e2 dug3 ki dug3-ga du3-a\ne2 kecki ki dug3-ga du3-a\n",
      "translatedText": "Good house, built in a place so good and fair,\nKesh house, built in a place so good and fair.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "ma2-gur8 nun-gin7 an-na dirig-ga\nma2-gur8 kug-gin7 ka2 si ri-a\nma2 an-na-gin7 muc3 kur-kur-ra\nu5 ma2 ban3-da-gin7 pec10-ta sur-sur-ra\n",
      "translatedText": "Like a princely barge, it floats upon the sky,\nLike a holy barge, with horns it sails on high.\nLike the boat of heaven, the jewel of the land,\nLike a cabin boat, it glides from off the strand.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 gud-gin7 ur5 ca4 ninda2-gin7 gu3 nun di\ne2 cag4-bi-ta lipic kalam-ma\na-ga-bi-ta zi ki-en-gi-ra\n",
      "translatedText": "House like a lowing bull, like a bull that bellows loud,\nWithin its heart, the land's own pulse is proud.\nFrom its rear, the life of Sumer is endowed.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 eb gal an-ne2 us2-sa\ne2 zid-da gal an-ne2 us2-sa\ne2 men gal an-ne2 us2-sa\ne2 dtir-an-na an-ne2 us2-sa\n",
      "translatedText": "Great shrine of the heavens, reaching to the sky,\nGreat righteous house, reaching to the sky,\nGreat crown of a house, reaching to the sky,\nHouse of the rainbow, reaching to the sky.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 muc3-bi an cag4-ga la2-a\nte-me-bi abzu-a sig9-ga\njissu-bi kur-kur-ra dul-la\n",
      "translatedText": "Its jewel in heaven's heart, a wondrous view,\nIts foundations in the Abzu deep are laid,\nIts shadow over all the lands is displayed.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 an-ne2 ki jar-ra den-lil2-le za3-mi2 dug4-ga\nama dnin-tu-ra ec-bar kij2 dug4-ga\ne2 kecki gurun-na sig7-ga\n",
      "translatedText": "House founded by An, by Enlil praised in song,\nFor Mother Nintu, where the oracles belong.\nHouse of Kesh, with fruit it grows so green.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "kecki-gin7 rib-ba lu2 ci-in-ga-tum2-mu\nur-saj-bi dacac7-gi4-gin7 rib-ba ama ci-in-ga-u3-tud\nnin-bi dnin-tud-gin7 rib-ba-ra a-ba-a igi mu-ni-in-du8\n",
      "translatedText": "Will any man bring forth a thing so great as Kesh has been?\nWill any mother bear a hero like Ashgi, so bold?\nWho has seen a lady like Nintud, of beauty untold?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 2-kam-ma",
      "translatedText": "The second house.",
      "type": "verse"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapterTitle": "House 3",
  "notes": "This section emphasizes the cosmic dimensions and dual nature of the temple, contrasting its heavenly height with its earthly depth using animal, celestial, and elemental metaphors.",
  "chunks": [
    {
      "originalText": "e2 an-ce3 10 car2iku ki-ce3 5 car2iku\ne2 an-ce3 10 bur3iku ki-ce3 5 bur3iku\n",
      "translatedText": "Ten units high to heaven, five units deep in earth,\nTen measures high to heaven, five measures deep in earth.\n",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 an-ce3 alim ki-ce3 lu-lim\ne2 an-ce3 ceg9-bar ki-ce3 tarah-mac\ne2 an-ce3 ceg9-bar gun3-a ki-ce3 tarah-mac sig7-ga\n",
      "translatedText": "A bison for the heavens, a stag for earth below,\nA wild ram for the heavens, a goat for earth below,\nA dappled ram for heaven, a fair goat for the earth.\n",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 an-ce3 muc mir-re-gin7 sig7-ga ki-ce3 u5mucen-gin7 a-e cu2-a\ne2 an-ce3 ud-gin7 ed2-a ki-ce3 iti6-gin7 barag2-ga\n",
      "translatedText": "Like fierce snakes in the heavens, like ducks on water's berth,\nLike sun that rises heavenward, like moon on earth outspread.\n",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 an-ce3 cita2 cul ki-ce3 jictun3-am3\ne2 an-ce3 kur-ra-am3 ki-ce3 idim-ma-am3\n",
      "translatedText": "A hero's mace for heaven, an axe for earth's own bed,\nA mountain for the heavens, a spring for earth's own floor.\n",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 an-ce3 3-kam-bi na-nam\n",
      "translatedText": "The house for the third time is truly this and more.\n",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "kecki-gin7 rib-ba lu2 ci-in-ga-an-tum2-mu\nur-saj-bi dacac7-gi4-gin7 rib-ba ama ci-in-ga-u3-tud\nnin-bi dnin-tud-gin7 rib-ba-ra a-ba-a igi mu-ni-in-du8\ne2 3-kam-ma",
      "translatedText": "Will any man bring forth a thing so great as Kesh has been?\nWill any mother bear a hero like Ashgi, so bold?\nWho has seen a lady like Nintud, of beauty untold?\nThe third house.",
      "type": "verse"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapterTitle": "House 4",
  "notes": "This section describes the temple as a bustling city and a site of ritual perfection, using animal and nature imagery to convey its majesty.",
  "chunks": [
    {
      "originalText": "iriki ga-am3 iriki ga-am3 cag4-bi a-ba mu-zu\ne2 kecki iriki ga-am3 cag4-bi a-ba mu-zu\n",
      "translatedText": "A city, oh, a city! Who knows what lies within?\nThe house of Kesh, a city! Who knows what lies within?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "cag4-bi ur-saj-ur-saj-e-ne si mu-un-si-sa2-e-ne\nec-bar kij2 dug4-ga cu gal mu-un-du7-du7\n",
      "translatedText": "Within its walls the heroes set all things in their place,\nDecisions made and labors done with perfect, holy grace.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 gud du7-du7-dam gu2 am3-ma-gur-re\ne2 gud car2-a al-gu7-e\ne2 udu car2-a-am3 al-gu7-e\n",
      "translatedText": "The house is like a perfect bull that bellows loud and deep,\nIt eats a myriad of bulls, a harvest it shall keep,\nIt eats a myriad of rams, and flocks of grazing sheep.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "X X-ma-am3 gu2-bi luh-luh-ha\nbarag-barag-e-ne gu2-ne am3-ma-jal2-le-ne\n",
      "translatedText": "Its neck is washed and purified within the sacred hall,\nThe rulers bow their heads to it, the masters of them all.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "jictaskarin-da men an-da-gur3-ru\njicasal2-gin7 an-da-tal2-tal2 sal-la\nhur-saj-da an-da-sig7-sig7-ga\n",
      "translatedText": "With boxwood crown it stands aloft, a glory to behold,\nLike poplars spreading wide and far, its branches manifold,\nAs verdant as the mountain range, in beauty yet untold.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "kecki-gin7 rib-ba lu2 ci-in-ga-an-tum2-mu\nur-saj-bi dacac7-gi4-gin7 rib-ba ama ci-in-ga-u3-tud\nnin-bi dnin-tud-gin7 rib-ba-ra a-ba-a igi mu-ni-in-du8\n",
      "translatedText": "Will any man bring forth a thing so great as Kesh has been?\nWill any mother bear a hero like Ashgi, so bold?\nWho has seen a lady like Nintud, of beauty untold?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 4-kam-ma",
      "translatedText": "The fourth house.",
      "type": "verse"
    }
  ]
}

