    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 caj4-mac-bi a-da-ab-ba\nal-jar-bi kuccem3-am3\ntigi-bi cem5-ma-am3\nza-am-za-am-bi gi-di-da-am3",
      "translatedText": "The house's wild boar is the adab-song,\nIts algar-lyre is the drum's deep beat,\nIts tigi-drums are the tambourines,\nIts zam-zam instruments are the reed-pipes sweet.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 nar-bi u3-ma-am3\nsipa-bi ud-da-am3\ne2 lu2 tigi-ba nar mu-un-tar-re\nzam-zam-ma u3-ma mu-un-tar-re",
      "translatedText": "The house's singer is a triumph song,\nIts shepherd is the light of day,\nThe house where tigi-players lead the choir,\nAnd zam-zam songs of victory hold sway.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 a-tu5-a-ba gud huc-am3\nluh-luh-ha-ba ud-gin7 car2-ra-am3",
      "translatedText": "Within its lustration room, a fierce bull stands,\nIts cleansing rites are bright as sunlight's glow.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "kecki-gin7 rib-ba lu2 ci-in-ga-tum2-mu\nur-saj-bi dacac7-gi4-gin7 rib-ba ama ci-in-ga-u3-tud\nnin-bi dnin-tud-gin7 rib-ba-ra a-ba-a igi mu-ni-in-du8",
      "translatedText": "Will any man bring forth a thing so great as Kesh has been?\nWill any mother bear a hero like Ashgi, so bold?\nWho has seen a lady like Nintud, of beauty untold?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 7-kam-ma",
      "translatedText": "The seventh house.",
      "type": "verse"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapterTitle": "House 8",
  "notes": "The final house of the Kesh Temple Hymn serves as a grand doxology, calling for joy throughout the cosmos and the temple, while repeating the refrain regarding the uniqueness of Kesh, its hero Ashgi, and its goddess Nintud.",
  "chunks": [
    {
      "originalText": "an-ki-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 kecki-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 dacac7-gi4-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 dnin-hur-saj-ja2-ka asil-la2 te-ma-ab",
      "translatedText": "In heaven and earth, let there be joy,\nIn the house of Kesh, let there be joy,\nIn the house of Ashgi, let there be joy,\nIn the house of Ninhursag, let there be joy.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "an-ki-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 kecki-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 nam-ti-la asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 zi-da asil-la2 te-ma-ab",
      "translatedText": "In heaven and earth, let there be joy,\nIn the house of Kesh, let there be joy,\nIn the house of life, let there be joy,\nIn the faithful house, let there be joy.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 dingir-re-ne asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 kug-ga asil-la2 te-ma-ab\ne2 me-te-na asil-la2 te-ma-ab\nkecki-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab",
      "translatedText": "In the house of the gods, let there be joy,\nIn the holy house, let there be joy,\nIn the house of fitting praise, let there be joy,\nIn Kesh itself, let there be joy.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "ud-de3 nam-lugal-la asil-la2 te-ma-ab\niti6-e nam-ensi2-ka asil-la2 te-ma-ab\nmu-e nam-nin-a asil-la2 te-ma-ab",
      "translatedText": "In the days of kingship, let there be joy,\nIn the months of lordship, let there be joy,\nIn the years of queenship, let there be joy.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "ud-ba asil-la2 te-ma-ab\nitima-ba asil-la2 te-ma-ab",
      "translatedText": "In its daylight, let there be joy,\nIn its inner chambers, let there be joy.",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "kecki-gin7 rib-ba lu2 ci-in-ga-tum2-mu\nur-saj-bi dacac7-gi4-gin7 rib-ba ama ci-in-ga-u3-tud\nnin-bi dnin-tud-gin7 rib-ba-ra a-ba-a igi mu-ni-in-du8",
      "translatedText": "Will any man bring forth a thing so great as Kesh has been?\nWill any mother bear a hero like Ashgi, so bold?\nWho has seen a lady like Nintud, of beauty untold?",
      "type": "verse"
    },
    {
      "originalText": "e2 8-kam-ma",
      "translatedText": "The eighth house. ",
      "type": "verse"
    }
  ]
}
